---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Jeff Melton - DevOps & Platform Engineering Consultant">
    <style>
        /* Hero Section */
        .hero {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 4rem 0;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 3rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .hero p {
            font-size: 1.25rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }

        .cta-button {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #e74c3c;
            color: white;
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-weight: 600;
            transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
        }

        .cta-button:hover {
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        /* Main Content Sections */
        .section {
            padding: 4rem 2rem;
        }

        .section:nth-child(even) {
            background: #f8f9fa;
        }

        .section h2 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            margin-left: 2rem;
            color: #2c3e50;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .section p {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            margin-left: 2rem;
            margin-right: 2rem;
            max-width: 800px;
        }

        /* Case Studies Grid */
        .case-studies-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr));
            gap: 2rem;
            margin: 3rem 2rem 2rem 2rem;
        }

        .case-study-card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 2rem;
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            transition: transform 0.3s;
        }

        .case-study-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
        }

        .case-study-card h3 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            color: #2c3e50;
        }

        .case-study-card p {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            font-size: 1rem;
        }

        .read-more {
            color: #3498db;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .read-more:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        /* Responsive Design */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .hero h1 {
                font-size: 2.5rem;
            }

            .hero p {
                font-size: 1.1rem;
            }

            .section h2 {
                font-size: 2rem;
            }

            .case-studies-grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }

            .container {
                padding: 0 1rem;
            }
        }

        @media (max-width: 480px) {
            .hero {
                padding: 3rem 0;
            }

            .hero h1 {
                font-size: 2rem;
            }
        }
    </style>

    <section class="hero" id="home">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>DevOps & Platform Engineering Consultant</h1>
            <p>I work across the entire problem-solving lifecycle‚Äîfrom identifying systemic issues that span multiple domains, to designing comprehensive solutions that address root causes, to building and implementing the technical platforms that make those solutions sustainable.</p>
            <a href="#case-studies" class="cta-button">See My Work</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="what-i-do">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>What I Do</h2>
            <p>I specialize in diagnosing and solving technical problems that require both deep systems expertise and business context understanding. My work typically involves complex, multi-domain challenges where technical solutions must align with organizational realities and business objectives.</p>
            
            <p>Whether it's infrastructure that's constraining business growth, systems that don't integrate properly across departments, or operational processes that waste engineering resources‚ÄîI work from problem identification through solution design to technical implementation. I don't just identify what's broken; I understand why it matters to the business and build sustainable platforms that prevent similar problems from recurring.</p>

            <p>My approach combines technical depth with organizational insight, ensuring that solutions are not only technically sound but operationally viable and strategically aligned with business needs.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="tools">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Tools & Platform Engineering</h2>
            <p>I build comprehensive tooling platforms that transform operational friction into automated excellence. Rather than accepting enterprise constraints as unchangeable, I engineer solutions that work within real-world limitations while dramatically improving productivity and reliability.</p>
            
            <div class="case-studies-grid">
                <div class="case-study-card">
                    <h3>üè• Fleet Health Monitoring</h3>
                    <p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Manual cluster validation across 6000+ Kubernetes clusters took 5-10 days.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> Elixir-based concurrent health monitoring system.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> 99.9% time reduction (days to 8-12 minutes), 2000+ engineering hours saved annually.</p>
                    <a href="/tools" class="read-more">View Full Platform ‚Üí</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="case-study-card">
