                    <strong>Impact:</strong> 2-3 hours saved daily, 75% reduction in incident response time.</p>
                    <a href="/tools" class="read-more">View Full Platform ‚Üí</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="case-study-card">
                    <h3>üöÄ Infrastructure Management</h3>
                    <p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Complex GPU and VM lifecycle management across hybrid infrastructure required manual coordination.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> Intelligent automation with cross-system correlation and safety validation.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> $400K+ operational overhead reduction, eliminated manual errors.</p>
                    <a href="/tools" class="read-more">View Full Platform ‚Üí</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem; padding: 2rem; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 10px;">
                <h3 style="color: #2c3e50; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Platform Philosophy</h3>
                <p style="font-style: italic; color: #666; max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto;">
                    "Enterprise friction should be solved through engineering, not accepted as unchangeable constraint. Each tool represents a decision to automate rather than tolerate, integrate rather than context-switch, and optimize rather than accept suboptimal workflows."
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="case-studies">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Case Studies</h2>
            <div class="case-studies-grid">
                <div class="case-study-card">
                    <h3>Legacy Infrastructure Modernization</h3>
                    <p><strong>Challenge:</strong> InfoSec-mandated SLES 11 EOL upgrade across Fortune One retailer's 600+ locations while maintaining existing hardware to maximize asset depreciation.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> 18-month platform engineering transformation balancing compliance requirements with business constraints, building comprehensive operational capabilities.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> $2M+ cost avoidance, 150:1 location-to-engineer efficiency, zero-downtime migrations with sustainable Day One operations.</p>
                    <a href="/case-studies/legacy-infrastructure-modernization" class="read-more">Read Full Case Study ‚Üí</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="case-study-card">
                    <h3>Platform Engineering at Scale</h3>
                    <p><strong>Challenge:</strong> 6000+ Kubernetes cluster infrastructure with 5-10 day manual validation cycles costing ~$40M annually in downtime risk.<br>
                    <strong>Solution:</strong> Engineered concurrent monitoring platform and integrated operations toolkit using Elixir, Rust, and Go.<br>
                    <strong>Impact:</strong> $400K+ cost avoidance, 99.9% time reduction (days to minutes), 2000+ engineering hours reclaimed annually.</p>
                    <a href="/case-studies/platform-engineering" class="read-more">Read Full Case Study ‚Üí</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="case-study-card">
                    <h3>Legacy System Modernization</h3>
                    <p>Designed and implemented a migration strategy for aging infrastructure, ensuring business continuity while systematically updating core systems and improving operational efficiency.</p>
                    <a href="/case-studies/modernization" class="read-more">Read Full Case Study ‚Üí</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="approach">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>My Approach</h2>
            <p>Every organization is different, but the patterns of technical debt and systemic dysfunction are remarkably consistent. I start by understanding not just what's broken, but why it broke ‚Äì what organizational or technical constraints led to the current state.</p>
            
            <p>Then I design solutions that work within your actual constraints, not theoretical ideal conditions. This often means building tools and processes that route around organizational limitations while gradually addressing root causes.</p>
            
            <p>The goal isn't just to solve the immediate problem, but to leave you with better systems, clearer processes, and the tools to prevent similar issues in the future.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>